main event: A round, saucer-shaped object was observed in the sky over Gainesville, Florida in October 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as being red, blue, and white in color.
The object disappeared straight up after being observed for about 20 minutes.
The investigation officer stated that the object was likely a weather balloon released by the Tampa and Miami weather stations.
The sighting was reported third-hand, with the information coming from the Jacksonville ARTC Center, relayed from the Gainesville Flight Service and Radio.
The exact location of the sighting was not provided.
photographs: No photographs present in the document
